# cs-email — project standards

## Scope

Customer-support email AI assistant implemented with **LangGraph** using the [Thinking in LangGraph](https://docs.langchain.com/oss/python/langgraph/thinking-in-langgraph) pattern (nodes, typed state, `Command` routing, checkpointers for `interrupt()`). Prefer **small, focused changes** that match existing graph and node patterns.

## Safety and privacy

- Never log or persist **raw email bodies, headers, or addresses** unless explicitly required; prefer redacted or hashed identifiers in logs.
- **Secrets**: load API keys and tokens only from **environment variables** or a secrets manager — never hardcode or commit them.
- Do not commit `.env` or local credential files.

## Quality bar

- Prefer **explicit errors** over silent failures; surface actionable messages for operators.
- When tests exist (`pytest`), run the relevant suite after non-trivial changes. When lint/format tools exist (`ruff`, etc.), run them before considering work done.
- Match **imports, typing, and structure** of surrounding code.

## Documentation

- Update **[AGENTS.md](AGENTS.md)** when you add entrypoints, layout, or standard commands so humans and the agent stay aligned.
